	<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
	<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:opsz,wght@9..40,400;9..40,500;9..40,600&family=Instrument+Serif&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

	<header class="nav">
		<div class="container nav-inner">
			<a href="/" class="nav-brand">
				<img src="/nudge-icon.png" alt="" width="32" height="32" />
				<span>Nudge</span>
			</a>
			<a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Back to home</a>
		</div>
	</header>

	<main class="container">
		<article class="legal">
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class="updated">Last updated: March 20, 2026</p>

			<p>Enrique Flores ("we", "our", "us"), operating through 404tf.com, develops and operates the Nudge application ("App") for Clover POS devices. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>

			<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
			<p>When you use the App, we access the following data through the Clover platform:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Order Data:</strong> Current order line items (product names, quantities, prices) to generate real-time suggestions</li>
				<li><strong>Inventory Data:</strong> Your product catalog and inventory levels to ensure suggestions reference available items</li>
				<li><strong>Customer Data:</strong> If available through Clover's customer system, order history associated with returning customers to personalize suggestions. No payment card data or personally identifiable end-customer information is collected.</li>
				<li><strong>Usage Statistics:</strong> Aggregated metrics such as suggestions shown, accepted, and dismissed</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>To generate AI-powered upsell and cross-sell suggestions during active orders</li>
				<li>To personalize suggestions based on customer purchase history when available</li>
				<li>To display performance statistics within the App</li>
				<li>To improve the quality and relevance of suggestions over time</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>3. AI Data Processing</h2>
			<p>Order context (product names, quantities, and prices from the current order) is sent to <strong>Z.AI (Zhipu AI)</strong>, our third-party AI service provider, to generate suggestions. According to Z.AI's privacy policy, they do not store any content provided through their API — inputs are processed in real time and are not saved on their servers. No personally identifiable customer information (names, emails, phone numbers, or payment data) is transmitted to the AI provider.</p>

			<h2>4. Data Storage and Retention</h2>
			<p>Usage statistics (suggestion counts, acceptance rates, upsell history) are stored <strong>locally on your Clover device</strong> using on-device storage (SharedPreferences). We do not maintain a cloud database of your merchant data. Local data persists until you:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Clear the App's data through your device settings</li>
				<li>Uninstall the App</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
			<p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your data to third parties. Data is shared only in the following cases:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Z.AI (Zhipu AI):</strong> Order context is sent solely to generate suggestions, with no data retained by the provider</li>
				<li><strong>Legal obligations:</strong> When required by law, regulation, or legal process</li>
				<li><strong>Safety:</strong> To protect the rights or safety of users</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>6. International Data Transfers</h2>
			<p>Order context sent to Z.AI may be processed on servers located outside your country of residence, including in China. By using the App, you consent to this transfer. All transmissions are encrypted via HTTPS.</p>

			<h2>7. Data Security</h2>
			<p>We implement reasonable technical measures to protect your data, including:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>HTTPS encryption for all API communications</li>
				<li>No cloud storage of merchant data — statistics remain on-device</li>
				<li>Leveraging the Clover platform's built-in authentication and security model</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
			<p>You may:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Uninstall the App at any time, which stops all data access and removes local data</li>
				<li>Clear local statistics by clearing the App's data in device settings</li>
				<li>Contact us to request information about how your data is processed</li>
				<li>Request deletion of any data we may hold by emailing us</li>
			</ul>
			<p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information is collected and to request its deletion under the CCPA. We do not sell personal information. To exercise your rights, contact us at the email below.</p>

			<h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
			<p>The App is designed for business use on Clover POS devices and is not directed at individuals under the age of 18.</p>

			<h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
			<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected by the "Last updated" date above. Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>

			<h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
			<p>For questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at <strong>enriquefft@404tf.com</strong>.</p>
		</article>
	</main>

	<footer class="footer">
		<div class="container footer-inner">
			<span>&copy; 2026 Enrique Flores. All rights reserved.</span>
			<nav>
				<a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
				<a href="/eula">Terms</a>
			</nav>
		</div>
	</footer>
</body>
</html>

